      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "9405bd105fd7ab4f",
      "text": "[[Sortition]] was in widespread use in [[Athenian Democracy]] and Renaissance Florence and is still used in modern [[jury selection]]."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "02c0417bde6ecf11",
      "text": "In ancient Athenian democracy, sortition was therefore the traditional and primary method for appointing political officials, and its use was regarded as a principal characteristic of true democracy."
    },
